1
00:00:57,409 --> 00:00:59,984
Next, we have the greatest

2
00:01:00,089 --> 00:01:03,425
karate competition
in the State of California.

3
00:01:03,536 --> 00:01:07,810
The competitors
are Bruce Lee from Seattle,

4
00:01:07,922 --> 00:01:10,593
and the three-times champion
Hoffman,

5
00:01:10,707 --> 00:01:13,864
a ninth Dan holder.

6
00:01:29,122 --> 00:01:32,279
Ah, first time in the competition,
and you won't be winning.

7
00:01:32,394 --> 00:01:33,331
Sorry.

8
00:01:33,438 --> 00:01:34,720
No.

9
00:01:34,831 --> 00:01:36,362
My goal is to win.

10
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:38,485
But that's too hard for you.

11
00:01:38,591 --> 00:01:40,953
It's no fun if it's not hard.

12
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,571
Begin.

13
00:02:11,975 --> 00:02:13,256
Good!

14
00:02:13,368 --> 00:02:14,518
Bruce, come on!

15
00:02:31,539 --> 00:02:33,901
Continue on.

16
00:03:13,244 --> 00:03:14,834
Keep on. Keep on.

17
00:04:24,223 --> 00:04:27,416
Hoffman, get up!

18
00:04:35,259 --> 00:04:37,242
Ladies and gentlemen,

19
00:04:37,348 --> 00:04:42,558
the champion in this competition
is Mr. Bruce Lee!

20
00:04:59,244 --> 00:05:01,915
There he is!

21
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:04,533
Mr. Lee, is this your first time
in this kind of competition?

22
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,099
Oh, sir.
- Thanks.

23
00:05:06,207 --> 00:05:07,832
Never participated before.

24
00:05:07,947 --> 00:05:09,573
Tell us, then,

25
00:05:09,687 --> 00:05:11,491
how did you beat
the third consecutive champion

26
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:13,750
who holds a ninth Dan position,
Mr. Hoffman?

27
00:05:13,865 --> 00:05:15,490
Do you think it's luck?

28
00:05:15,606 --> 00:05:18,633
Nothing to do with luck.
Right here. It's a strength.

29
00:05:18,739 --> 00:05:21,730
One more question.
What level are you in karate?

30
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:25,940
Don't want to disappoint you,

31
00:05:26,049 --> 00:05:28,553
but that wasn't karate
I used back there just now.

32
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:32,031
What you saw me do back there
to that Hoffman was kung fu.

33
00:05:32,141 --> 00:05:34,396
Kung fu? What is kung fu?

34
00:05:34,509 --> 00:05:37,286
It's Chinese kung fu.

35
00:05:37,397 --> 00:05:40,246
Maybe you can't find it
in your dictionary,

36
00:05:40,356 --> 00:05:43,027
but, today, I, Bruce Lee,

37
00:05:43,142 --> 00:05:45,776
will add it to your dictionary.

38
00:06:28,883 --> 00:06:31,518
Here he is, Bruce Lee.

39
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:35,452
Hey, Bruce, congratulations.
- Bruce.

40
00:06:35,568 --> 00:06:36,921
Linda.

41
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:49,317
Tell me you didn't get hurt.

42
00:06:49,423 --> 00:06:51,500
Oh, no. Not even a single scratch.

43
00:06:51,616 --> 00:06:53,349
Great.

44
00:06:53,460 --> 00:06:57,496
He must be the man
you've been telling me about.

45
00:06:57,603 --> 00:07:00,559
Linda, let me introduce you
to Master James.

46
00:07:00,666 --> 00:07:02,470
He's my first kung fu master.

47
00:07:02,581 --> 00:07:04,527
Much like a father to me.

48
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:07,484
Bruce has often
mentioned you to me.

49
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:10,098
You should give him
more good ideas in the future.

50
00:07:10,205 --> 00:07:13,920
You should take some credit
for Bruce's success today.

51
00:07:14,034 --> 00:07:18,105
Thank you. But only if he can afford
to pay me a decent salary.

52
00:07:18,212 --> 00:07:21,653
I've already decided
that I'll pay you with my whole life.

53
00:07:37,427 --> 00:07:39,895
James, let's begin.

54
00:07:40,003 --> 00:07:41,557
Okay.

55
00:07:53,197 --> 00:07:54,965
I love kung fu so very much.

56
00:07:55,077 --> 00:07:57,296
I've been searching
for a Chinese kung fu school

57
00:07:57,409 --> 00:07:59,213
to study, and I've finally found one.

58
00:07:59,324 --> 00:08:00,474
It's great.

59
00:08:02,387 --> 00:08:03,776
Okay. This way, please.

60
00:08:03,884 --> 00:08:06,317
Hi. May I have your name?
- Hello. Jim.

61
00:08:07,923 --> 00:08:09,276
Good.
- Thank you.

62
00:08:09,384 --> 00:08:11,817
Yeah. You can go in.

63
00:08:13,144 --> 00:08:16,171
That Bruce Lee...
he must be out of his mind.

64
00:08:16,277 --> 00:08:18,260
For so many years,

65
00:08:18,366 --> 00:08:22,046
we Chinese set up
the kung fu schools in the US.

66
00:08:22,161 --> 00:08:25,982
We abide by the rule
"never teach the outsiders."

67
00:08:26,094 --> 00:08:29,394
Many years have passed,
and no one dared break this rule.

68
00:08:29,505 --> 00:08:32,461
But this Bruce Lee
went and recruited students

69
00:08:32,569 --> 00:08:35,690
using his title of karate champion.

70
00:08:35,806 --> 00:08:37,788
In his school, most of the students

71
00:08:37,895 --> 00:08:41,681
are either Caucasian or black
and Filipino and Japanese.

72
00:08:41,793 --> 00:08:45,829
That's exactly why I'll help Master Wang,
whom we respect,

73
00:08:45,936 --> 00:08:49,829
and stop Bruce Lee
in the name of Chinese kung fu.

74
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:52,646
Otherwise, our longstanding rule

75
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:57,246
of never teaching outsiders
will be destroyed by him.

76
00:08:58,434 --> 00:09:02,635
The only way to stop him
is to win by fighting.

77
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,661
What?

78
00:09:04,769 --> 00:09:08,354
What are you saying?
You know Bruce Lee?

79
00:09:08,459 --> 00:09:09,883
Not only do I know him,

80
00:09:09,991 --> 00:09:12,625
he and I have unfinished business.

81
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:22,723
Tø be honest,
the only reason I came here

82
00:09:22,837 --> 00:09:24,367
was for Bruce Lee.

83
00:09:25,447 --> 00:09:26,942
Look, Yellow.

84
00:09:27,049 --> 00:09:30,312
He's beaten the karate
champion of California.

85
00:09:30,426 --> 00:09:33,025
He must be extremely good.

86
00:09:33,141 --> 00:09:37,377
You better be very confident
to beat him.

87
00:09:39,825 --> 00:09:41,843
Don't worry, Master.

88
00:09:41,948 --> 00:09:43,966
I've been working very hard in Taiwan

89
00:09:44,071 --> 00:09:45,946
with only one thing in mind...

90
00:09:46,056 --> 00:09:48,038
me kicking his ass.

91
00:09:48,144 --> 00:09:50,126
He only uses Yong Chun Quan,

92
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:53,675
and all my techniques
are ready to beat his moves.

93
00:09:53,784 --> 00:09:56,775
Now I'm worried.

94
00:09:56,882 --> 00:09:59,244
He's afraid to face me.

95
00:10:01,164 --> 00:10:02,967
What happens when you win?

96
00:10:03,078 --> 00:10:04,811
I will follow the tradition.

97
00:10:04,924 --> 00:10:06,549
Make him announce it.

98
00:10:06,664 --> 00:10:10,593
Bruce Lee tells everyone
he lost to Wing Chun style.

99
00:10:14,844 --> 00:10:17,242
The school will shut down.

100
00:10:22,086 --> 00:10:25,207
Shifu, what are you thinking?

101
00:10:25,323 --> 00:10:27,306
Nothing.

102
00:10:27,412 --> 00:10:29,702
I want to remind you, on this matter,

103
00:10:29,814 --> 00:10:32,176
you can't do it on your own.

104
00:10:32,285 --> 00:10:37,780
If you pick a fight with him,
let me arrange it for you.

105
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:40,498
We'll do it aboveboard.

106
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,980
Good.

107
00:10:44,086 --> 00:10:45,510
Two.

108
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:50,239
Good. Three.

109
00:10:51,606 --> 00:10:53,445
Good. Let's do it together.

110
00:10:53,555 --> 00:10:55,180
One, two, three!

111
00:10:56,897 --> 00:10:59,223
Good. One, two, three!

112
00:10:59,334 --> 00:11:01,482
One, two, three!

113
00:11:10,439 --> 00:11:11,993
This way, sir.

114
00:11:13,293 --> 00:11:15,726
It's my honor to see you here, Mr. Lee.

115
00:11:15,835 --> 00:11:17,496
It's my honor, Master Wang.

116
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:19,556
Please, Bruce.

117
00:11:19,664 --> 00:11:21,883
Thanks for coming.
- Thank you.

118
00:11:21,996 --> 00:11:26,127
Bruce, I feel so happy
that you knocked out Hoffman.

119
00:11:26,243 --> 00:11:28,569
You made our Chinese
proud of ourselves.

120
00:11:28,680 --> 00:11:31,528
Have a seat.
We are so proud of you.

121
00:11:31,639 --> 00:11:34,107
A brilliant young man.

122
00:11:34,214 --> 00:11:38,001
Bruce, I was invited to come here

123
00:11:38,113 --> 00:11:40,997
to help our friends
and manage the business

124
00:11:41,108 --> 00:11:44,027
of the Chinese Kung Fu Association.

125
00:11:46,712 --> 00:11:52,481
I'd like for you to verify
the contents in these letters are true.

126
00:11:55,311 --> 00:11:58,017
The main thing is, your school in Seattle

127
00:11:58,130 --> 00:12:00,243
is a Chinese kung fu school,

128
00:12:00,359 --> 00:12:02,341
which is very important.

129
00:12:02,447 --> 00:12:05,711
Absolutely. It is indeed true.

130
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:08,816
However, I must say,

131
00:12:08,922 --> 00:12:11,628
the students you have
are not all Chinese.

132
00:12:11,742 --> 00:12:15,327
You're saying the international
students enrolled?

133
00:12:15,432 --> 00:12:19,598
Yes. I've heard you've indeed
accepted many of them.

134
00:12:19,714 --> 00:12:21,660
Tø be honest,

135
00:12:21,767 --> 00:12:23,298
in my kung fu school,

136
00:12:23,404 --> 00:12:26,252
80% of the students
are foreigners.

137
00:12:26,363 --> 00:12:28,381
This is going to be a problem.

138
00:12:28,486 --> 00:12:31,678
Listen to me, Bruce, many Chinese

139
00:12:31,793 --> 00:12:34,986
have opened kung fu schools
to teach in America,

140
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:38,127
but none of them has done like you.

141
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:39,931
For a long time,

142
00:12:40,044 --> 00:12:42,714
everyone here has been following
this unofficial rule

143
00:12:42,828 --> 00:12:45,427
of teaching only Chinese students.

144
00:12:45,544 --> 00:12:48,500
I invited you here for a talk today.

145
00:12:48,607 --> 00:12:54,280
I hope you can correct your mistake
by expelling all the outsiders

146
00:12:54,386 --> 00:12:56,534
to avoid complaints from others.

147
00:12:56,649 --> 00:13:01,966
Master, these rules
don't help us develop Chinese kung fu.

148
00:13:03,158 --> 00:13:08,653
If we want our kung fu to move forward,
we have to abandon these old rules.

149
00:13:10,504 --> 00:13:12,687
Mr. Bruce Lee,
haven't you ever thought

150
00:13:12,801 --> 00:13:16,623
about the consequences
of teaching students from other countries?

151
00:13:18,127 --> 00:13:20,417
Isn't karate from Japan?

152
00:13:20,529 --> 00:13:24,600
The Japanese brought it to America
and made it available to all.

153
00:13:24,706 --> 00:13:26,996
You can see karate clubs everywhere.

154
00:13:28,292 --> 00:13:30,096
There are national, even international

155
00:13:30,207 --> 00:13:32,984
karate competitions in America.

156
00:13:35,045 --> 00:13:37,894
If the Japanese had never done this,

157
00:13:38,004 --> 00:13:40,437
would karate even
be popular in America?

158
00:13:40,546 --> 00:13:44,261
All right, Mr. Lee. I get it.

159
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:49,178
Mr. Lee, I was trying to be nice,
but let's forget that.

160
00:13:51,023 --> 00:13:57,706
Master Wang, it looks like we're...
having a Hongmen Banquet today.

161
00:13:57,812 --> 00:14:01,361
Well, then, on behalf of the association,

162
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:06,297
I advise you to obey all the rules
and behave yourself.

163
00:14:19,569 --> 00:14:21,896
Higher. Higher.

164
00:14:23,155 --> 00:14:26,906
Your hands, higher. Higher.

165
00:14:27,019 --> 00:14:28,717
Master, look.

166
00:14:36,523 --> 00:14:39,965
Hello, sir. You must be sent
by Master Wang.

167
00:14:40,073 --> 00:14:41,533
Yes.

168
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:44,453
On behalf of Chinese
Kung Fu Association,

169
00:14:44,564 --> 00:14:46,059
here is an invitation of challenge.

170
00:14:47,631 --> 00:14:48,781
A challenge?

171
00:14:48,881 --> 00:14:51,100
Yes.

172
00:14:53,998 --> 00:14:56,882
Now, what if I accept
the challenge I've been given?

173
00:14:56,991 --> 00:14:59,424
And what if I don't? Then what?

174
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:03,604
If you accept,
there will be a winner or loser.

175
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:05,763
If you are the loser,
you will have to accept

176
00:15:05,869 --> 00:15:07,981
all requirements from the association.

177
00:15:08,096 --> 00:15:10,731
You have to do whatever they say.

178
00:15:10,846 --> 00:15:14,074
You have two choices
from which to pick.

179
00:15:14,188 --> 00:15:16,657
Either stop teaching the outsiders,

180
00:15:16,765 --> 00:15:19,304
or shut down your kung fu school.

181
00:15:19,410 --> 00:15:22,710
Okay, I'll accept your challenge.

182
00:15:31,803 --> 00:15:34,580
Bruce Lee!

183
00:15:51,959 --> 00:15:54,771
Yellow Skin. Is that you?

184
00:15:56,623 --> 00:15:58,284
You didn't expect me?

185
00:15:58,399 --> 00:16:00,096
It's unexpected indeed.

186
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:03,200
Bruce Lee,

187
00:16:03,308 --> 00:16:07,794
doesn't matter you've defeated
Americans or Japanese.

188
00:16:07,902 --> 00:16:11,724
But today, you will lose to me.

189
00:16:13,716 --> 00:16:15,306
You are just a ghost.

190
00:16:15,421 --> 00:16:19,208
Right. I am a ghost.

191
00:16:20,748 --> 00:16:25,056
Wherever you go,
I will never leave you.

192
00:16:25,169 --> 00:16:30,558
In fact, I think we came up
with a winner years ago.

193
00:16:32,097 --> 00:16:36,132
Tøday, we are just going to fight,

194
00:16:36,239 --> 00:16:38,814
have a competition
in front of everyone.

195
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:40,902
This way,

196
00:16:41,008 --> 00:16:42,991
let everyone watch,

197
00:16:43,097 --> 00:16:47,857
let them see how you will fall
right in front of me,

198
00:16:47,970 --> 00:16:49,668
and that's that.

199
00:17:00,990 --> 00:17:02,865
You're done.

200
00:17:16,342 --> 00:17:17,517
So, then, let's fight!

201
00:21:44,843 --> 00:21:45,993
Stop!

202
00:21:47,314 --> 00:21:50,614
That's it!
- I'm not done yet.

203
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:52,803
I haven't lost yet.
- I said stop!

204
00:21:52,919 --> 00:21:54,616
I did win, didn't I?

205
00:21:54,729 --> 00:21:57,577
From now, I can teach whomever I like

206
00:21:57,688 --> 00:22:00,536
and do whatever I want
with my kung fu school.

207
00:22:01,935 --> 00:22:03,489
This is great.
- It's great.

208
00:22:07,331 --> 00:22:08,506
Let's go.

209
00:22:08,619 --> 00:22:09,769
Oh, Bruce!

210
00:22:35,737 --> 00:22:37,470
Bruce!

211
00:22:38,591 --> 00:22:41,226
Careful. Careful.

212
00:23:01,707 --> 00:23:04,448
Bruce...

213
00:23:16,153 --> 00:23:17,993
I can't fall.

214
00:23:22,071 --> 00:23:23,530
I must stand up.

215
00:23:30,878 --> 00:23:33,620
What did the doctor say?

216
00:23:36,379 --> 00:23:38,456
We're still waiting for the result.

217
00:23:38,572 --> 00:23:40,969
I will tell you as soon as we get it.

218
00:23:42,645 --> 00:23:46,122
Jesse, let's go ask the doctor what's up.

219
00:23:46,230 --> 00:23:48,663
All right.
- Okay. Let's go.

220
00:23:58,835 --> 00:23:59,986
Linda?

221
00:24:00,086 --> 00:24:01,746
Yeah?

222
00:24:03,462 --> 00:24:05,479
Do I look very ugly?

223
00:24:05,586 --> 00:24:07,948
No.

224
00:24:08,057 --> 00:24:10,490
What did the doctor say?

225
00:24:10,598 --> 00:24:13,898
He said you would be fine.

226
00:24:15,298 --> 00:24:18,669
Linda?
- Yes?

227
00:24:18,779 --> 00:24:22,566
Don't lie to me. Tell me the truth.

228
00:24:24,488 --> 00:24:26,566
Just from their look,

229
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:30,677
I could see my injury
must be severe.

230
00:24:30,789 --> 00:24:33,364
Bruce, please don't think so much.

231
00:24:33,469 --> 00:24:35,796
You'll recover and be fine.

232
00:24:37,925 --> 00:24:41,296
Fortunately, we still have our baby.

233
00:24:41,406 --> 00:24:43,733
Bruce, don't talk so much.

234
00:24:43,844 --> 00:24:47,072
Control your emotions.
He will be fine.

235
00:24:47,185 --> 00:24:54,186
If our little son Brandon
saw his father like this,

236
00:24:55,644 --> 00:25:01,176
I think our little Brandon
would feel very sad.

237
00:25:01,283 --> 00:25:03,610
He won't be sad, Bruce.

238
00:25:03,721 --> 00:25:05,074
Proud.

239
00:25:13,537 --> 00:25:16,599
Doctor, please don't comfort me.

240
00:25:16,705 --> 00:25:17,987
I need to know his real condition.

241
00:25:18,097 --> 00:25:19,723
Please sit down, Mrs. Lee.

242
00:25:19,839 --> 00:25:21,499
I don't want to waste your time.

243
00:25:21,613 --> 00:25:23,523
Your husband's injury
is much worse.

244
00:25:23,633 --> 00:25:25,615
Tell me if he's paralyzed forever.

245
00:25:25,722 --> 00:25:27,704
Your husband's backbone
is severely injured.

246
00:25:27,810 --> 00:25:29,994
I would even say shifted.
- What?

247
00:25:30,108 --> 00:25:32,125
I don't care about the backbone.

248
00:25:32,231 --> 00:25:34,830
I need the final result.

249
00:25:39,577 --> 00:25:41,831
He will never stand up, will he?

250
00:25:41,943 --> 00:25:46,537
Well, we can hardly find
any fat in his whole body,

251
00:25:46,643 --> 00:25:48,625
only incredible muscles.

252
00:25:48,732 --> 00:25:53,385
If he's mentally strong,
he may live in a wheelchair.

253
00:25:53,501 --> 00:25:56,658
Wheelchair?

254
00:25:58,270 --> 00:26:01,153
Spend his life in a wheelchair?

255
00:26:01,264 --> 00:26:05,715
Like I said, Linda,
I can't even say if he can stand up,

256
00:26:05,824 --> 00:26:07,806
not to mention continuing his karate

257
00:26:07,913 --> 00:26:10,025
which I'm sure his body won't allow.

258
00:26:10,140 --> 00:26:13,024
No. It's Chinese kung fu.

259
00:26:13,134 --> 00:26:15,318
Okay. Chinese kung fu.

260
00:26:18,913 --> 00:26:21,584
Is he ever gonna be able to walk?

261
00:26:21,698 --> 00:26:23,952
Only if there's a miracle.

262
00:26:44,499 --> 00:26:46,268
What is it, Linda?

263
00:26:48,468 --> 00:26:51,007
Did the doctor tell you

