00:49:10,624 --> 00:49:12,878
the strength's from waist and arms,

529
00:49:12,991 --> 00:49:14,901
while Yong Chun Quan...

530
00:49:15,010 --> 00:49:17,681
the strength's from
the stroke of your whole body.

531
00:49:17,795 --> 00:49:19,741
Therefore, you can strike a deadly blow

532
00:49:19,849 --> 00:49:21,130
within an inch.

533
00:49:21,241 --> 00:49:22,391
Come show him.

534
00:49:24,513 --> 00:49:25,866
Take it.

535
00:50:30,864 --> 00:50:32,217
Morning, Master.

536
00:50:34,624 --> 00:50:38,066
So, did you actually
run here just now?

537
00:50:38,174 --> 00:50:40,287
Yes. Based on your instructions.

538
00:50:40,403 --> 00:50:41,957
10 kilometers a day...

539
00:50:42,073 --> 00:50:44,257
5 coming here and 5 back home.

540
00:50:44,371 --> 00:50:46,174
Good. You must keep it going.

541
00:50:46,286 --> 00:50:48,363
Master, what are you
gonna teach me today?

542
00:50:51,646 --> 00:50:54,245
You see the corner of the wall?

543
00:50:54,362 --> 00:50:56,866
Go there and practice horse squatting.

544
00:50:56,973 --> 00:50:58,633
Horse squatting?

545
00:50:58,748 --> 00:51:01,038
Master, I want to learn actual combat.

546
00:51:01,150 --> 00:51:03,203
Horse squatting I can do at home.

547
00:51:03,308 --> 00:51:05,254
Shut up.

548
00:51:05,363 --> 00:51:07,416
Go horse squatting now.

549
00:51:10,375 --> 00:51:12,214
Yes, Master.

550
00:52:09,938 --> 00:52:12,051
Morning, Master.
- Morning.

551
00:52:13,558 --> 00:52:17,273
Master, do you mind if I practice
with my brothers today?

552
00:52:17,387 --> 00:52:19,784
I've been horse squatting
for a week now.

553
00:52:21,530 --> 00:52:25,245
Shun Leung, go work
on strengthening his wrists.

554
00:52:25,359 --> 00:52:27,613
Let's go.

555
00:52:41,755 --> 00:52:43,701
Let's go, Bruce.

556
00:52:48,265 --> 00:52:50,863
Bruce, can you lift it up?

557
00:52:50,980 --> 00:52:52,678
Yeah. Of course I can.

558
00:52:52,790 --> 00:52:54,072
Like this?

559
00:52:54,183 --> 00:52:57,102
No, not like that.

560
00:52:57,212 --> 00:52:59,466
Grab it from one end

561
00:52:59,579 --> 00:53:01,597
and lift evenly

562
00:53:01,702 --> 00:53:03,577
while horse squatting.

563
00:53:08,107 --> 00:53:10,089
Let me do it.

564
00:53:12,390 --> 00:53:14,787
You see? I can lift it evenly.

565
00:53:17,333 --> 00:53:19,279
Can you hold it still for an hour?

566
00:53:19,386 --> 00:53:23,801
Brother, can I please skip practice
on this useless nonsense?

567
00:53:23,912 --> 00:53:25,537
It's ridiculous.

568
00:53:25,652 --> 00:53:27,800
I don't want to spend
my vacation this way.

569
00:53:27,915 --> 00:53:31,701
You'll achieve nothing
without basic practice.

570
00:53:31,814 --> 00:53:34,413
Just do what Master asks you to do.

571
00:53:34,530 --> 00:53:37,129
Master, Bruce is still practicing.

572
00:53:54,094 --> 00:53:56,076
Bruce, it's almost done.

573
00:53:56,182 --> 00:53:58,960
Take a break now.
- Leave me alone.

574
00:54:03,493 --> 00:54:05,570
It seems you think
I didn't keep my words,

575
00:54:05,686 --> 00:54:08,677
didn't you?

576
00:54:08,784 --> 00:54:12,012
But do you know why
I keep asking you to squat?

577
00:54:13,553 --> 00:54:16,295
I guess you still don't
understand the essence of kung fu.

578
00:54:16,408 --> 00:54:18,390
Essence?

579
00:54:18,496 --> 00:54:21,000
What were you thinking
while horse squatting?

580
00:54:21,107 --> 00:54:23,184
What could I think?

581
00:54:23,300 --> 00:54:26,219
I was thinking
why you changed your mind.

582
00:54:26,328 --> 00:54:27,824
What else?

583
00:54:27,930 --> 00:54:30,957
Whatever you ask me, I'll do it.

584
00:54:31,063 --> 00:54:32,380
Don't worry, Master.

585
00:54:32,490 --> 00:54:34,923
I'll keep horse squatting
well till you say so.

586
00:54:35,032 --> 00:54:38,332
Yes, Bruce,
you've wasted time so far.

587
00:54:38,443 --> 00:54:41,327
Lots of time.

588
00:54:41,437 --> 00:54:43,656
Why? I don't understand.

589
00:54:43,769 --> 00:54:46,096
Do you know why you have to squat?

590
00:54:48,121 --> 00:54:52,916
Master James told me
that horse squatting is practice.

591
00:54:53,030 --> 00:54:55,736
Can't learn kung fu
without practicing.

592
00:54:55,849 --> 00:54:57,403
So I'm practicing.

593
00:54:57,520 --> 00:55:00,191
I thought you'd teach me the real thing
sooner or later.

594
00:55:00,305 --> 00:55:02,417
If you want me to lift the pole forever,

595
00:55:02,533 --> 00:55:04,823
I'll just do it.

596
00:55:04,935 --> 00:55:07,368
So Master James

597
00:55:07,476 --> 00:55:09,553
has taught you the importance
of horse squatting.

598
00:55:09,669 --> 00:55:13,384
However, you didn't get
the core of it, you see?

599
00:55:13,498 --> 00:55:15,825
Horse squatting is a basic skill

600
00:55:15,935 --> 00:55:20,588
for all kung fu artists to master first.

601
00:55:20,704 --> 00:55:22,923
Horse squatting is not only

602
00:55:23,037 --> 00:55:26,028
for strengthening your legs,
but more importantly,

603
00:55:26,135 --> 00:55:28,709
it is to strengthen your mind.

604
00:55:28,815 --> 00:55:30,725
The key of kung fu training

605
00:55:30,835 --> 00:55:32,817
is to train your mind.

606
00:55:32,923 --> 00:55:34,727
Train your mind

607
00:55:34,838 --> 00:55:37,128
is to strengthen your mind and spirit.

608
00:55:37,240 --> 00:55:38,735
What, squatting can train your mind?

609
00:55:38,841 --> 00:55:41,512
That's right, Bruce. You're too anxious.

610
00:55:41,626 --> 00:55:43,608
What's vital to kung fu training

611
00:55:43,714 --> 00:55:47,607
is to make both your body and mind

612
00:55:47,718 --> 00:55:50,781
as calm as still water.

613
00:55:50,886 --> 00:55:54,328
A calm mind can reach
a thousand miles away.

614
00:55:54,436 --> 00:55:56,869
A thousand miles away.

615
00:55:56,978 --> 00:56:00,870
While you're horse squatting,
you're like a tree.

616
00:56:00,981 --> 00:56:05,182
Just imagine yourself
as a big tree reaching the sky.

617
00:56:05,298 --> 00:56:07,873
No matter how tall it is,

618
00:56:07,978 --> 00:56:11,206
it stands on its root, you know?

619
00:56:11,320 --> 00:56:13,539
So your entire body and mind

620
00:56:13,653 --> 00:56:17,783
should take root
into the earth under your feet.

621
00:56:17,899 --> 00:56:20,154
<i>The deeper your root gets,</i>

622
00:56:20,266 --> 00:56:23,185
<i>the better your kung fu is.</i>

623
00:56:23,295 --> 00:56:25,894
<i>Kung fu training means
to build yourself up</i>

624
00:56:26,011 --> 00:56:27,921
<i>from the inside out.</i>

625
00:56:28,029 --> 00:56:30,012
<i>That eventually integrates</i>

626
00:56:30,118 --> 00:56:32,231
<i>with all creatures on earth.</i>

627
00:56:32,347 --> 00:56:34,780
<i>If you can reach this level,</i>

628
00:56:34,887 --> 00:56:37,806
<i>your entire body and mind</i>

629
00:56:37,916 --> 00:56:41,702
<i>will then turn into water...</i>

630
00:56:41,815 --> 00:56:45,292
<i>from a big tree to water</i>

631
00:56:45,400 --> 00:56:49,816
<i>which can infiltrate to everything on earth.</i>

632
00:56:49,926 --> 00:56:51,837
<i>At that time,</i>

633
00:56:51,945 --> 00:56:55,910
<i>you will reach an even higher level
of kung fu training.</i>

634
00:56:56,018 --> 00:56:59,080
<i>Only when you integrate yourself
into water consciously,</i>

635
00:56:59,186 --> 00:57:01,440
<i>or unconsciously,</i>

636
00:57:01,553 --> 00:57:03,736
<i>can your body and mind integrate</i>

637
00:57:03,850 --> 00:57:06,069
<i>into the earth beneath you.</i>

638
00:57:09,142 --> 00:57:15,089
<i>Only by then can you get the true spirit
of kung fu.</i>

639
00:57:38,349 --> 00:57:40,817
Master is back.

640
00:57:40,925 --> 00:57:41,862
Master.

641
00:57:41,969 --> 00:57:44,224
Master is back.
- Master.

642
00:57:49,454 --> 00:57:51,436
Keep practicing.

643
00:58:17,999 --> 00:58:20,218
Did you ask him
to lift two poles together?

644
00:58:20,331 --> 00:58:22,871
No. He did it himself.

645
00:58:22,977 --> 00:58:26,348
I've been out so long.
Has he been doing it?

646
00:58:26,459 --> 00:58:28,821
Absolutely.
It's been the whole day.

647
00:58:33,142 --> 00:58:34,388
Good boy.

648
00:58:34,499 --> 00:58:36,482
He has the makings of a kung fu artist.

649
00:58:36,588 --> 00:58:38,606
Originally, he didn't like
this kind of boring stuff.

650
00:58:38,712 --> 00:58:41,596
But he did it against your will.

651
00:58:43,168 --> 00:58:45,221
What a character.

652
00:59:13,349 --> 00:59:16,091
Mind your posture.

653
00:59:27,239 --> 00:59:28,937
Looks good.

654
00:59:43,217 --> 00:59:44,748
Master.

655
00:59:44,853 --> 00:59:46,551
Bruce,

656
00:59:46,663 --> 00:59:48,253
from now on,

657
00:59:48,369 --> 00:59:50,482
you may practice
with your elder brother

658
00:59:50,598 --> 00:59:53,339
and see how that feels.

659
00:59:53,452 --> 00:59:56,123
Really? That's awesome!

660
00:59:56,237 --> 00:59:58,420
Go. Practice over there. Just go.

661
00:59:59,578 --> 01:00:01,109
Thanks, Master.

662
01:00:55,521 --> 01:00:58,928
Slow down. Don't drag me.
- Hurry up.

663
01:00:59,037 --> 01:01:01,671
Why did you take me here
in the early morning?

664
01:01:01,787 --> 01:01:05,015
Do you want to get beaten again?
- Hey, you go in there.

665
01:01:05,129 --> 01:01:08,156
Think of a way to get Yellow Skin out.

666
01:01:08,262 --> 01:01:09,817
Aw, Bruce,

667
01:01:09,932 --> 01:01:12,080
I can't help you this time.

668
01:01:12,195 --> 01:01:13,893
You've just recovered.

669
01:01:14,005 --> 01:01:17,554
You can't do anything...
but get beaten up all day.

670
01:01:17,661 --> 01:01:19,988
You go in now.

671
01:01:20,098 --> 01:01:22,425
Okay. I know.

672
01:01:26,155 --> 01:01:29,596
Go in!
- Okay, I'll go.

673
01:01:29,706 --> 01:01:31,474
What should I tell him, huh?

674
01:01:31,586 --> 01:01:35,716
Just tell him his rival is here.

675
01:01:41,472 --> 01:01:43,027
What did you say?

676
01:01:45,475 --> 01:01:48,359
Whose rival is he?
- Of course it's yours.

677
01:01:48,469 --> 01:01:51,044
It's mine?

678
01:01:51,150 --> 01:01:53,227
I might like to learn
a few tricks from you.

679
01:02:00,235 --> 01:02:04,721
It seems I didn't kick you
hard enough last time.

680
01:02:04,831 --> 01:02:07,193
Tøday would you like me
to break your ribs

681
01:02:07,302 --> 01:02:08,762
or your legs first?

682
01:02:11,654 --> 01:02:14,325
What if I broke your ribs
or your legs?

683
01:02:14,439 --> 01:02:15,589
What, then?

684
01:02:20,286 --> 01:02:22,861
Then I'll say you're great.

685
01:02:25,091 --> 01:02:26,824
Come on.

686
01:02:34,420 --> 01:02:37,268
Hey, Bruce, why do you
ask for trouble?

687
01:02:37,380 --> 01:02:39,457
Leave me alone.

688
01:03:38,612 --> 01:03:40,345
Just kick.

689
01:03:40,458 --> 01:03:42,606
Kick, you idiot.

690
01:04:03,433 --> 01:04:05,415
Shun Leung, begin.

691
01:04:05,522 --> 01:04:06,875
Right away.

692
01:04:06,984 --> 01:04:08,265
Yes, Master.

693
01:04:08,376 --> 01:04:10,002
Jun Lee, you'll be defending.

694
01:04:11,753 --> 01:04:13,866
Come here.

695
01:04:13,981 --> 01:04:15,262
Master.

696
01:04:15,374 --> 01:04:16,798
Bruce.

697
01:04:18,507 --> 01:04:22,613
Well, you two go get ready.

698
01:04:22,719 --> 01:04:25,425
Make sure to go beyond that.

699
01:04:25,539 --> 01:04:27,793
Get it? Ready? Begin.

700
01:04:33,336 --> 01:04:36,363
Bruce, when fighting
with Yong Chun Quan,

701
01:04:36,469 --> 01:04:38,522
don't stick to the rules and tricks.

702
01:04:38,628 --> 01:04:41,405
Fight whatever you feel like.

703
01:05:00,245 --> 01:05:02,298
Billy, go on.

704
01:05:31,854 --> 01:05:33,800
Good job.

705
01:05:33,908 --> 01:05:36,615
Good job.

706
01:05:36,728 --> 01:05:38,639
Way to go.

707
01:05:38,747 --> 01:05:40,372
Brother, are you okay?

708
01:05:40,487 --> 01:05:42,920
No. You've used inch punch.

709
01:05:43,029 --> 01:05:45,082
I did it involuntarily.

710
01:05:45,187 --> 01:05:47,858
Wow. You did it in such a short time.

711
01:05:47,972 --> 01:05:50,298
Really awesome.
- You got it.

712
01:05:50,409 --> 01:05:51,999
Good job.

713
01:05:52,115 --> 01:05:56,115
Bruce, although you just fought
with the inch punch,

714
01:05:56,222 --> 01:05:58,691
your level of skill wasn't good enough.

715
01:05:58,798 --> 01:06:00,780
Little did your brother expect

716
01:06:00,887 --> 01:06:02,905
you could learn do it
in such a short time.

717
01:06:03,010 --> 01:06:04,992
He underestimates you.

718
01:06:05,099 --> 01:06:07,389
That made you a very lucky guy.

719
01:06:10,216 --> 01:06:11,771
But, Bruce,

720
01:06:11,887 --> 01:06:14,285
you can't always count
on luck to save you all the time.

721
01:06:14,393 --> 01:06:16,720
Yes. I didn't expect it, either.

722
01:06:16,831 --> 01:06:21,626
I think Bruce's punches
are quite powerful now.

723
01:06:21,739 --> 01:06:25,075
Bruce, to learn a certain boxing,

724
01:06:25,185 --> 01:06:27,298
action is the foundation.

725
01:06:27,413 --> 01:06:30,155
Your brother has taught you about it.

726
01:06:30,268 --> 01:06:32,772
But you want to make it perfect.

727
01:06:32,879 --> 01:06:34,932
You have to put
your whole heart into it,

728
01:06:35,037 --> 01:06:37,612
and it takes a long time to master it.

729
01:06:37,717 --> 01:06:40,495
Get the board. Give her a try.

730
01:06:42,139 --> 01:06:43,289
Try this.

731
01:06:45,933 --> 01:06:47,084
Okay.

732
01:06:49,762 --> 01:06:51,222
Get more strength.

733
01:06:56,516 --> 01:06:59,542
You see, you've got the essentials
of the inch punch.

734
01:06:59,649 --> 01:07:02,426
But to smash the board
with one punch

735
01:07:02,538 --> 01:07:04,615
is not training you can do in one day.

736
01:07:04,732 --> 01:07:07,236
What you're learning
now, Bruce, see,

737
01:07:07,342 --> 01:07:09,324
is real kung fu.

738
01:07:09,431 --> 01:07:14,440
The rules of action, hands and steps
will be of less importance.

739
01:07:14,548 --> 01:07:18,228
If keeping practicing, everyone can get it.

740
01:07:18,343 --> 01:07:21,464
Tø simply put, get power from feet

741
01:07:21,580 --> 01:07:23,799
and punch out from the heart,

742
01:07:23,913 --> 01:07:26,061
attack whenever you can,

743
01:07:26,175 --> 01:07:28,323
and defend each inch of land.

744
01:07:28,438 --> 01:07:30,170
Again, simply put,

745
01:07:30,283 --> 01:07:32,431
you get power from feet,

746
01:07:32,545 --> 01:07:34,598
punch out from the heart,

747
01:07:34,704 --> 01:07:36,649
and simply attack when you can,

748
01:07:36,758 --> 01:07:38,740
and defend each inch of land!

749
01:07:38,847 --> 01:07:41,137
Get power from your feet

750
01:07:41,248 --> 01:07:43,325
and punch out from the heart,

751
01:07:43,441 --> 01:07:45,387
attack whenever you can,

752
01:07:45,495 --> 01:07:47,050
and defend each inch of land.

753
01:07:47,166 --> 01:07:49,492
It's like a kid holding a concave mirror

754
01:07:49,603 --> 01:07:51,621
to emblaze paper with collected sunlight.

755
01:07:51,727 --> 01:07:55,312
The theory is that the concave mirror

756
01:07:55,416 --> 01:07:58,716
converges sunlight to one final point, no?

757
01:07:58,828 --> 01:08:00,738
Which emblazes things.

758
01:08:00,848 --> 01:08:02,164
I got it, Master.

759
01:08:02,275 --> 01:08:05,301
Also, utilize the power

760
01:08:05,408 --> 01:08:07,069
of your opponent.
- You mean

761
01:08:07,183 --> 01:08:10,731
utilizing the rival's power
to get back and attack him

762
01:08:10,838 --> 01:08:14,031
quickly enough to save our energy.

763
01:08:14,146 --> 01:08:17,101
You'll understand it more
when thinking about it.

764
01:08:17,209 --> 01:08:19,571
I believe in your perception.

765
01:08:19,680 --> 01:08:22,636
The core of real kung fu
is that while attacking,

766
01:08:22,743 --> 01:08:24,689
you should focus all your power

767
01:08:24,798 --> 01:08:27,017
on one point and attack in a second.

768
01:08:27,129 --> 01:08:29,040
While defending,

769
01:08:29,149 --> 01:08:31,060
eliminate the rival's attack

770
01:08:31,168 --> 01:08:34,468
and turn your defense mode to offense

771
01:08:34,580 --> 01:08:37,571
with the suddenness of a thunderbolt!

772
01:08:45,859 --> 01:08:49,265
<i>You have to reach the unity
of offense and defense,</i>

773
01:08:49,375 --> 01:08:51,974
<i>the harmony of yin and yang.</i>

774
01:08:52,089 --> 01:08:54,760
<i>This is the level you should achieve</i>

775
01:08:54,875 --> 01:08:57,652
<i>when fighting with Yong Chun Quan.</i>

776
01:08:57,764 --> 01:08:59,389
<i>In other words,</i>

777
01:08:59,504 --> 01:09:01,831
<i>your attack includes defense,</i>

778
01:09:01,941 --> 01:09:05,526
<i>and within your defense,
hides offense.</i>

779
01:09:05,631 --> 01:09:09,275
<i>The speed and skill
of the transition between the two</i>

780
01:09:09,391 --> 01:09:13,700
<i>is what kung fu artists
need to master.</i>

781
01:09:13,812 --> 01:09:15,545
Prepare.

782
01:09:41,452 --> 01:09:46,081
Bruce, I always admired you as a man,

783
01:09:48,241 --> 01:09:51,612
and you're a hero in my heart,

784
01:09:51,721 --> 01:09:55,364
but now... you're different,

785
01:09:57,987 --> 01:10:01,109
and I thought...

786
01:10:01,226 --> 01:10:04,454
you have a side of weakness

787
01:10:04,567 --> 01:10:06,680
and cowardice.

788
01:10:08,919 --> 01:10:11,317
But we can't do anything about it.

789
01:10:16,124 --> 01:10:19,222
You're Bruce Lee.

790
01:10:19,327 --> 01:10:23,885
Find a way to make it work.
You see?

791
