I've never heard of this kind of thing.

1055
01:31:51,076 --> 01:31:54,339
Well, I'd like to meet
this Yamamoto again.

1056
01:32:04,269 --> 01:32:06,073
Well, if it isn't Bruce Lee.

1057
01:32:06,184 --> 01:32:08,367
Am I not welcome?

1058
01:32:09,874 --> 01:32:12,236
I didn't teach you
a good lesson last time.

1059
01:32:12,345 --> 01:32:15,573
Aren't you asking for trouble?

1060
01:32:32,571 --> 01:32:35,348
Bruce Lee, you are such a nuisance.

1061
01:32:35,461 --> 01:32:38,309
I don't intend
on spying on your training.

1062
01:32:40,438 --> 01:32:42,516
I've just come to deliver
my challenge invitation.

1063
01:32:42,631 --> 01:32:44,162
You don't have the eligibility.

1064
01:32:44,267 --> 01:32:45,371
I have.

1065
01:32:45,486 --> 01:32:46,767
Get lost.

1066
01:32:49,455 --> 01:32:51,472
Bring it on.

1067
01:33:03,727 --> 01:33:05,780
Bruce?

1068
01:33:13,753 --> 01:33:16,875
Where's Bruce?
- Where could he be?

1069
01:33:16,990 --> 01:33:18,973
Could he be at school training?

1070
01:33:20,262 --> 01:33:22,624
No. I just came back
from there. He wasn't there.

1071
01:33:24,231 --> 01:33:25,381
Oh, God.

1072
01:33:25,484 --> 01:33:27,988
I bet he went to visit Yamamoto.

1073
01:33:28,095 --> 01:33:29,412
We should go.

1074
01:33:36,416 --> 01:33:38,528
Don't come back!

1075
01:33:41,219 --> 01:33:43,581
Let's go.
- Are you okay?

1076
01:34:04,125 --> 01:34:07,567
Bruce, you're not sleepy?

1077
01:34:07,676 --> 01:34:09,302
I can't sleep.

1078
01:34:10,531 --> 01:34:15,539
If I don't go compete
with various masters,

1079
01:34:15,648 --> 01:34:19,612
how would I know the core
of their exquisite skills?

1080
01:34:22,610 --> 01:34:25,114
Kimora, I want to set up my own style.

1081
01:34:25,221 --> 01:34:26,396
Your own style?

1082
01:34:26,509 --> 01:34:29,108
That's right. My own style.

1083
01:34:29,224 --> 01:34:31,064
Well, that's not easy.

1084
01:34:31,173 --> 01:34:34,271
When I was little,

1085
01:34:34,376 --> 01:34:38,756
I learned from Master James
Tang Lang Quan, Shaolin Quan,

1086
01:34:38,867 --> 01:34:43,175
Hong Quan, Chang Quan,
and many other styles.

1087
01:34:43,288 --> 01:34:48,154
Later on, I learned from Master Ye
his Yong Chun Quan.

1088
01:34:48,266 --> 01:34:50,805
And after that, I felt Yong Chun Quan

1089
01:34:50,911 --> 01:34:53,024
was the most powerful one
in the world.

1090
01:34:53,140 --> 01:34:55,846
Later on, I joined
on the Western boxing team

1091
01:34:55,959 --> 01:34:59,544
and found there was something
useful as well.

1092
01:35:01,459 --> 01:35:06,017
Now I realize some secret tricks
in Japanese karate.

1093
01:35:06,125 --> 01:35:08,273
Oh, right.

1094
01:35:09,431 --> 01:35:10,962
More and more,

1095
01:35:11,068 --> 01:35:13,050
I feel that each style

1096
01:35:13,157 --> 01:35:15,969
has its own advantage
and disadvantage

1097
01:35:16,080 --> 01:35:19,380
which can be studied and utilized.

1098
01:35:19,492 --> 01:35:23,658
Now, I haven't known
enough boxing styles,

1099
01:35:23,773 --> 01:35:26,515
but I believe that through
my studying and research

1100
01:35:26,628 --> 01:35:28,776
of the various boxing styles,

1101
01:35:28,891 --> 01:35:30,801
I can improve Yong Chun Quan

1102
01:35:30,911 --> 01:35:32,465
and make it a more practical one.

1103
01:35:33,625 --> 01:35:35,394
Improve Yong Chun Quan?

1104
01:35:35,505 --> 01:35:36,655
Right.

1105
01:35:38,185 --> 01:35:41,972
Bruce, why don't we sit down
with Professor Klein

1106
01:35:42,084 --> 01:35:43,995
and discuss it further,

1107
01:35:44,104 --> 01:35:46,466
creating a new way for kung fu together?
- You got it.

1108
01:35:48,943 --> 01:35:50,296
Good.

1109
01:35:53,746 --> 01:35:57,331
UNIVERSITY OF WASHING TON

1110
01:36:27,235 --> 01:36:29,775
Professor Klein,

1111
01:36:29,881 --> 01:36:32,765
I know that I have to learn
a lot of knowledge about martial arts.

1112
01:36:32,874 --> 01:36:36,316
I need to understand the essences
of various schools...

1113
01:36:36,426 --> 01:36:40,497
analyzing, comparing,
and doing research.

1114
01:36:40,603 --> 01:36:43,036
And for achieving my goal,
I have no better way

1115
01:36:43,143 --> 01:36:46,514
but to compete
with those masters from each school.

1116
01:36:46,625 --> 01:36:50,969
That way, I can discover
which school is practical and which is not.

1117
01:36:51,081 --> 01:36:52,742
You know what, Bruce Lee?

1118
01:36:52,857 --> 01:36:55,598
Rodin once said,
"It's not a lack of beauty in life

1119
01:36:55,711 --> 01:36:57,621
but the eyes to discover."

1120
01:36:57,730 --> 01:37:00,993
In your case, it means
it's not a lack of master of martial arts

1121
01:37:01,107 --> 01:37:02,911
but the eyes to discover.

1122
01:37:03,021 --> 01:37:05,905
You may have to compete
with yourself after all.

1123
01:37:06,015 --> 01:37:09,243
Compete with myself?
- Yes.

1124
01:37:09,357 --> 01:37:12,064
One's biggest rival is none but himself.

1125
01:37:12,176 --> 01:37:14,431
I guess you've chosen a philosophy major,

1126
01:37:14,544 --> 01:37:17,641
which is the best way to find out
how to compete with yourself.

1127
01:37:17,747 --> 01:37:20,939
And what's more,
my understanding of martial arts

1128
01:37:21,054 --> 01:37:23,593
is that it isn't just
for building up your body,

1129
01:37:23,700 --> 01:37:25,919
nor competing with your rival.

1130
01:37:26,031 --> 01:37:28,464
The biggest benefit
for studying martial arts

1131
01:37:28,573 --> 01:37:31,670
is probably a way
of an appreciation of cultures.

1132
01:37:31,776 --> 01:37:34,244
Young man, you should make
the best use of your time

1133
01:37:34,352 --> 01:37:38,458
to study and figure out how to create
your own theory for martial arts.

1134
01:37:38,564 --> 01:37:40,617
I believe that you have such potential.

1135
01:38:59,709 --> 01:39:03,531
Our jujitsu is the most
powerful skill of combat.

1136
01:39:03,643 --> 01:39:06,491
No other combat styles can defeat us.

1137
01:39:07,577 --> 01:39:08,727
Come over.

1138
01:39:12,067 --> 01:39:14,702
Aim it. Come on.

1139
01:39:14,817 --> 01:39:18,153
Make him unbalanced at first.

1140
01:39:18,263 --> 01:39:21,361
And then it'll be easier.

1141
01:39:21,466 --> 01:39:23,164
This is called defending with one blow.

1142
01:39:40,473 --> 01:39:46,942
Yong Chun Quan has its strong points
and its limitations, too.

1143
01:39:47,053 --> 01:39:50,768
Are you still thinking
about Willy Jay's jujitsu?

1144
01:39:52,170 --> 01:39:56,241
We should learn anything
useful to us.

1145
01:39:58,541 --> 01:40:00,974
Well, let's send him
a challenge invitation.

1146
01:40:03,519 --> 01:40:08,077
I have a challenge invitation that says
Bruce Lee wants to compete with me.

1147
01:40:08,183 --> 01:40:10,925
Bruce Lee wants to compete
with you now?

1148
01:40:11,038 --> 01:40:13,577
I bet he doesn't want to lose his ribs.

1149
01:40:13,684 --> 01:40:15,523
James, I don't understand all this.

1150
01:40:17,025 --> 01:40:21,156
Bruce Lee is such a small
and slim guy at only 140 pounds.

1151
01:40:21,273 --> 01:40:23,776
I mean, I won't waste more time on this.

1152
01:40:23,883 --> 01:40:25,164
Where will it take place?

1153
01:40:25,276 --> 01:40:26,557
In a public venue.

1154
01:40:26,668 --> 01:40:28,128
You're competing in a public venue?

1155
01:40:28,234 --> 01:40:29,588
I've never heard of such a thing.

1156
01:40:29,697 --> 01:40:31,466
Yeah, he's crazy.

1157
01:40:31,576 --> 01:40:34,175
I think he's too arrogant.

1158
01:40:34,292 --> 01:40:36,274
Completely arrogant.

1159
01:40:36,381 --> 01:40:38,849
Only a maniac would take
his own life lightly.

1160
01:40:38,956 --> 01:40:41,176
Don't you think?
- James, what do you want to talk about?

1161
01:40:41,289 --> 01:40:44,316
Well, it's about the match.

1162
01:40:44,422 --> 01:40:47,306
There's gonna be
a supervisor there officiating.

1163
01:40:47,416 --> 01:40:48,590
Who?

1164
01:40:48,704 --> 01:40:50,543
Inosando.

1165
01:40:50,653 --> 01:40:52,492
That guy.

1166
01:40:52,603 --> 01:40:54,478
He's a professor at a sports college.

1167
01:40:54,587 --> 01:40:56,213
Right. Right.

1168
01:40:56,327 --> 01:40:59,449
You know what? He's famous for
the "King of Filipino Stick."

1169
01:40:59,565 --> 01:41:01,784
Really? It sounds great.

1170
01:41:28,632 --> 01:41:32,489
Mr. Willy Jay.
- Hello, Mr. Lee.

1171
01:41:32,601 --> 01:41:34,298
After you.

1172
01:41:35,595 --> 01:41:37,577
Come.

1173
01:41:44,297 --> 01:41:47,075
Tøday, the master
of Bruce Lee Kung Fu Club,

1174
01:41:47,187 --> 01:41:49,098
Mr. Bruce Lee,

1175
01:41:49,206 --> 01:41:51,710
will challenge Mr. Willy Jay,

1176
01:41:51,817 --> 01:41:54,915
the master of Willy Ja Jujitsu Club.

1177
01:41:55,019 --> 01:41:57,002
As the host of this game today,

1178
01:41:57,108 --> 01:41:59,363
I'd like to invite Professor Inosando

1179
01:41:59,475 --> 01:42:02,146
from the Sport Academy
to be our supervisor.

1180
01:42:02,261 --> 01:42:04,800
The rule of the game is

1181
01:42:04,907 --> 01:42:09,595
as long as one party makes the other
unable to stand up again,

1182
01:42:09,710 --> 01:42:12,808
he declares victory.

1183
01:42:12,913 --> 01:42:16,011
Both parties get ready.

1184
01:42:16,116 --> 01:42:18,787
Is that clear?

1185
01:42:18,900 --> 01:42:21,369
Is that clear?

1186
01:42:23,112 --> 01:42:25,402
Professor Inosando.

1187
01:42:33,626 --> 01:42:35,500
Are you ready?

1188
01:42:35,610 --> 01:42:37,164
Now begin.

1189
01:44:12,804 --> 01:44:13,954
Yeah!

1190
01:45:15,499 --> 01:45:17,718
Go on. Go on with it.

1191
01:45:40,633 --> 01:45:44,419
This is Bruce Lee's fight.

1192
01:45:48,361 --> 01:45:50,343
Your jujitsu is really powerful.

1193
01:45:50,449 --> 01:45:51,695
Thank you, Mr. Lee.

1194
01:45:51,807 --> 01:45:54,097
You didn't make a fool of me
in front of everybody.

1195
01:45:54,209 --> 01:45:57,473
I knew you showed me some mercy,
allowing me to have the upper hand.

1196
01:45:57,586 --> 01:45:58,974
I knew it, Mr. Lee.

1197
01:45:59,083 --> 01:46:02,346
And even if you went all the way,
maybe I couldn't keep my feet.

1198
01:46:02,460 --> 01:46:05,760
And also, you dominated me
when falling to the ground.

1199
01:46:05,871 --> 01:46:09,349
If you'd used the eyeball trick,
I'd have been blinded already.

1200
01:46:12,311 --> 01:46:15,682
I think I understand what you want
isn't for winning or losing

1201
01:46:15,792 --> 01:46:19,828
but to get to know me,
or I'll say to improve your skills

1202
01:46:19,935 --> 01:46:22,225
by learning from my jiujitsu.

1203
01:46:22,337 --> 01:46:23,832
Is that right?

1204
01:46:23,938 --> 01:46:26,407
Correct. You've got it.

1205
01:46:26,514 --> 01:46:29,089
Now, I try to compete
with various masters.

1206
01:46:29,194 --> 01:46:31,901
My goal isn't for winning

1207
01:46:32,014 --> 01:46:35,836
but to improve my kung fu
to a higher level.

1208
01:46:35,948 --> 01:46:39,140
So I hope you can help me,
Master Willy Jay.

1209
01:46:39,255 --> 01:46:40,988
I appreciate it.

1210
01:46:41,101 --> 01:46:44,056
It's my honor to teach you
my jujitsu, Mr. Lee.

1211
01:46:45,835 --> 01:46:48,862
Thank you.
Thank you so much, Master Jay.

1212
01:47:28,548 --> 01:47:30,458
Class is dismissed.

1213
01:47:42,681 --> 01:47:45,079
Bruce! Bruce, the professor is here.

1214
01:47:47,590 --> 01:47:50,224
Professor Inosando.

1215
01:47:50,340 --> 01:47:53,331
We've met before.

1216
01:47:54,866 --> 01:47:56,848
Yes.

1217
01:47:56,955 --> 01:47:58,414
I just want to know,

1218
01:47:58,521 --> 01:48:00,360
when you were competing
with Willy Jay,

1219
01:48:00,471 --> 01:48:03,390
why did you hold back?

1220
01:48:03,499 --> 01:48:05,482
I don't want to just beat Willy Jay

1221
01:48:05,588 --> 01:48:11,012
and lose the chance to learn
and study jujitsu together with him.

1222
01:48:14,152 --> 01:48:16,169
Would you please
give me a chance like that?

1223
01:48:16,275 --> 01:48:18,814
You're too humble.

1224
01:48:18,920 --> 01:48:22,742
I've heard you're a great martial artist
with high achievements.

1225
01:48:22,854 --> 01:48:24,907
I haven't had a chance to learn from you.
- Flattering.

1226
01:48:25,012 --> 01:48:26,472
Okay, well, watch out.

1227
01:48:31,453 --> 01:48:33,292
You're indeed fast.

1228
01:48:33,402 --> 01:48:35,171
Let's see who's faster.

1229
01:48:40,886 --> 01:48:42,832
Thanks for the opportunity.

1230
01:48:42,940 --> 01:48:45,409
I admit defeat.

1231
01:48:45,516 --> 01:48:47,011
You're too modest.

1232
01:48:52,688 --> 01:48:54,005
Professor Ino,

1233
01:48:54,115 --> 01:48:56,749
I feel that Filipino boxing
is quite flexible,

1234
01:48:56,865 --> 01:48:59,263
with rapid speed
and the various changes,

1235
01:48:59,371 --> 01:49:01,282
but it is not powerful enough.

1236
01:49:01,390 --> 01:49:04,452
Yong Chun Quan's key
is simple and direct.

1237
01:49:04,559 --> 01:49:08,202
It requires you to launch attack
while defending yourself.

1238
01:49:08,318 --> 01:49:10,572
This is the crucial characteristic of it.

1239
01:49:10,685 --> 01:49:13,153
But there are weaknesses
in its footwork.

1240
01:49:13,261 --> 01:49:15,860
It's quite useful at a closer distance,

1241
01:49:15,976 --> 01:49:19,763
but it doesn't work well
between the middle to long range.

1242
01:49:31,780 --> 01:49:34,593
Kimura, I'd like to promote
our kung fu club

1243
01:49:34,705 --> 01:49:37,376
in a really big way in the community.

1244
01:49:37,490 --> 01:49:39,638
I still truly believe in the importance

1245
01:49:39,752 --> 01:49:43,052
of exchanging ideas
with different schools.

1246
01:49:44,174 --> 01:49:45,633
But how?

1247
01:49:45,740 --> 01:49:47,722
Breaking into their schools?

1248
01:49:47,828 --> 01:49:49,941
Well, come.

1249
01:49:53,050 --> 01:49:57,845
It's not a good idea
to challenge them at their door.

1250
01:49:57,959 --> 01:50:00,012
I suppose it'll be better

1251
01:50:00,117 --> 01:50:02,752
to ask for them to challenge us here

1252
01:50:02,868 --> 01:50:06,654
rather than we go to their door.

1253
01:50:09,795 --> 01:50:12,014
What are you dreaming again?

1254
01:50:12,127 --> 01:50:14,417
When you compete
with others in our club,

1255
01:50:14,530 --> 01:50:17,200
if you happen to lose
before our students,

1256
01:50:17,314 --> 01:50:18,489
it would be a shame.

1257
01:50:19,820 --> 01:50:23,120
My goal is to set up
a new style of boxing.

1258
01:50:23,232 --> 01:50:25,522
I don't care about winning or losing.

1259
01:50:25,634 --> 01:50:28,792
It's worth it even if I lose.

1260
01:50:30,508 --> 01:50:32,241
All right? Like this.

1261
01:50:33,432 --> 01:50:34,749
Write it down.

1262
01:50:38,235 --> 01:50:40,977
No matter, whenever,

1263
01:50:41,090 --> 01:50:44,912
wherever, and whoever

1264
01:50:45,024 --> 01:50:46,519
wants to challenge me,

1265
01:50:46,626 --> 01:50:48,085
I'm going to accept it.

1266
01:50:51,116 --> 01:50:53,822
Looks like Bruce Lee
is going to challenge...

1267
01:50:53,936 --> 01:50:55,740
the Americans.

1268
01:50:58,844 --> 01:51:00,232
Bruce Lee is challenging

1269
01:51:00,341 --> 01:51:02,109
the whole field of martial arts in America.

1270
01:51:02,221 --> 01:51:05,663
Bruce Lee has put up a sign
at the gate of his club,

1271
01:51:05,771 --> 01:51:08,893
saying anyone at any time at any place

1272
01:51:09,010 --> 01:51:11,585
wants to challenge him,
he's ready to accept.

1273
01:51:13,326 --> 01:51:15,308
Bruce is too damn arrogant.

1274
01:51:15,415 --> 01:51:17,634
He's out of his mind.

1275
01:51:19,105 --> 01:51:22,476
He had some nerve to come
and challenge me in my home.

1276
01:51:22,586 --> 01:51:26,229
So he came up with such an idea?

1277
01:51:26,345 --> 01:51:29,229
I'll smash his kung fu club.

1278
01:51:42,950 --> 01:51:45,098
Did you hear me?

1279
01:51:55,169 --> 01:51:58,161
What are you doing here?

1280
01:52:00,948 --> 01:52:03,203
Hello, Mr. Yamamoto.

1281
01:52:03,316 --> 01:52:06,128
I'm glad you're here to instruct me.

1282
01:52:07,702 --> 01:52:10,135
I'm only here
to see your kind of boxing.

1283
01:52:12,018 --> 01:52:14,866
I've been wanting
to learn from you, Master.

1284
01:52:14,977 --> 01:52:19,606
Thank you for paying me a visit.

1285
01:52:19,711 --> 01:52:21,621
I'm so thrilled to see you.

1286
01:52:21,730 --> 01:52:23,712
I'm warning you right now,

1287
01:52:23,818 --> 01:52:27,605
there is no place
for you in America, Bruce Lee.

1288
01:52:27,718 --> 01:52:30,008
You can't be so arrogant.

1289
01:52:30,120 --> 01:52:31,853
Whether I'm arrogant or not,

1290
01:52:31,965 --> 01:52:33,662
we'll find out after the match.

1291
01:52:33,775 --> 01:52:38,368
If you lose the game today,
you have to be my coach,

1292
01:52:38,475 --> 01:52:43,970
and I'll teach you Yong Chun Quan
and some other things.

1293
01:52:44,079 --> 01:52:46,441
You teach me?

1294
01:52:46,551 --> 01:52:49,364
Only if you beat me
will I accept any of your requests.

1295
01:52:49,475 --> 01:52:52,074
Come on.
- Good. Come on.

1296
01:54:51,664 --> 01:54:53,609
Master, my apologies.

1297
01:55:09,835 --> 01:55:11,568
Mr. Yamamoto.

1298
01:55:14,813 --> 01:55:18,220
You've made your promise,
and I really hope you can keep it, okay?

1299
01:55:18,329 --> 01:55:21,000
I'll visit you in a couple of days
to see how you're feeling.

1300
01:55:32,114 --> 01:55:34,404
Jesse, please put up the sign again.
- Sure.

1301
01:56:21,581 --> 01:56:23,207
Here's $20.

1302
01:56:23,322 --> 01:56:26,313
I'll bring the ice bucket back
a little later.

1303
01:56:32,442 --> 01:56:34,661
Come on, guys.
Let's get ready for class.

1304
01:56:34,775 --> 01:56:37,030
Tell us about your matches.
- Yeah.

1305
01:56:43,756 --> 01:56:45,595
Bruce Lee.

1306
01:57:00,848 --> 01:57:04,184
Have some ice.
- Okay.

1307
01:57:15,156 --> 01:57:16,686
I've met a real master.

1308
01:57:22,919 --> 01:57:25,352
You don't have to do that.

1309
01:57:25,461 --> 01:57:27,965
I just wanted to cool you down.

1310
01:57:29,638 --> 01:57:33,603
If you can beat me,
I'll cool down immediately.

1311
01:57:33,711 --> 01:57:36,559
Do you have any idea
how this will finish?

1312
01:57:36,670 --> 01:57:40,491
Of course. Only one of us
will walk outta here.

1313
01:57:40,603 --> 01:57:42,585
If that is the case,

1314
01:57:42,692 --> 01:57:45,160
why do you want to act
like a fool right now?

1315
01:57:45,268 --> 01:57:49,683
If I don't accept your challenge,
I'll be the idiot.

1316
01:57:49,794 --> 01:57:51,597
Bruce, forget it.

1317
01:57:51,708 --> 01:57:53,476
Tell them to leave.

1318
01:57:56,651 --> 01:57:59,570
Kimura, please take them out.

1319
01:58:05,006 --> 01:58:07,712
Let's go. Everyone. All of you.

1320
01:58:16,877 --> 01:58:19,796
You're a one-armed martial artist.

1321
01:59:27,300 --> 01:59:30,327
Your kung fu is really good.
Why don't you compete?

1322
01:59:30,433 --> 01:59:33,769
It's pretentious and makes me sick.

1323
01:59:33,879 --> 01:59:36,134
Cool guy.

1324
02:01:06,722 --> 02:01:08,775
I'm giving you a little lesson.

1325
02:01:10,063 --> 02:01:13,256
No one should ever be that arrogant.

1326
02:01:25,520 --> 02:01:27,110
Hey.

1327
02:02:05,275 --> 02:02:06,805
Bruce!

1328
02:02:09,069 --> 02:02:10,529
Bruce, did he hurt you?

1329
02:02:15,370 --> 02:02:17,174
He's smarter than me.

1330
02:02:17,284 --> 02:02:18,982
Master, can you beat him?

1331
02:02:19,094 --> 02:02:21,077
Bruce, what did he say to you?

1332
02:03:06,160 --> 02:03:08,759
Yong Chun Quan
has many advantages

1333
02:03:08,875 --> 02:03:10,858
as well as disadvantages.

1334
02:03:10,964 --> 02:03:12,982
I want to integrate the hand techniques

1335
02:03:13,087 --> 02:03:16,600
and footwork of jujitsu
into Yong Chun Quan.

1336
02:03:16,707 --> 02:03:20,873
I will also combine the footwork
of Western boxing with it.

1337
02:03:20,989 --> 02:03:22,971
After this improvement,

1338
02:03:23,078 --> 02:03:27,279
Yong Chun Quan will absorb the essence
of many other boxing techniques

1339
02:03:27,395 --> 02:03:31,881
and will eliminate the complicated
and unpractical stuff.

1340
02:03:47,272 --> 02:03:49,634
A new boxing style. Good paper.

1341
02:03:49,744 --> 02:03:53,565
Professor Klein,
do you see any problems with it?

1342
02:03:54,757 --> 02:03:57,985
I'm really pleased
to see the progress you've made.

1343
02:03:58,098 --> 02:04:01,849
Remember, I told you not long ago,
you should defeat yourself.

1344
02:04:01,963 --> 02:04:04,740
The biggest enemy is... yourself.

1345
02:04:04,852 --> 02:04:07,426
So now I see you have
revised your view on it.

1346
02:04:07,533 --> 02:04:09,646
But, still, there are a lot
of unanswered questions.

1347
02:04:09,760 --> 02:04:11,743
Please, have a seat.

1348
02:04:11,849 --> 02:04:13,759
Go ahead. Sit down.

1349
02:04:13,868 --> 02:04:15,256
Professor Klein,

1350
02:04:15,365 --> 02:04:17,762
I've been troubled by them for a while.

1351
02:04:21,074 --> 02:04:25,145
Oh, Bruce Lee, you are now quite clear
about the innovation of your new style.

1352
02:04:25,251 --> 02:04:27,684
You've used the power
your rival attacked you

1353
02:04:27,793 --> 02:04:29,775
to counterattack him.

1354
02:04:29,881 --> 02:04:32,516
As for the boxing,
it is your way of attacking.

1355
02:04:32,632 --> 02:04:36,002
As for styles,
there are too many variations, correct?

1356
02:04:36,113 --> 02:04:40,422
Bruce Lee, you must realize that the new
style that must be established...

1357
02:04:40,534 --> 02:04:42,551
Whoa. Hold on.

1358
02:04:42,658 --> 02:04:44,497
On the basis of Chinese philosophy,

1359
02:04:44,607 --> 02:04:46,268
will keep developing.

1360
02:04:46,382 --> 02:04:49,230
The new style created
is based on Chinese kung fu,

1361
02:04:49,341 --> 02:04:51,109
Both the Confucianism and Daoism

1362
02:04:51,221 --> 02:04:53,998
have influenced Chinese kung fu
tremendously.

1363
02:04:54,110 --> 02:04:56,887
The Confucianism
values harmony and moderation,

1364
02:04:57,000 --> 02:05:00,857
while the Daoism
focuses on dialectics and perception.

1365
02:05:00,968 --> 02:05:03,080
So, you can learn a lot
from other schools

1366
02:05:03,196 --> 02:05:06,781
and transplant them onto
the tree of Chinese kung fu.

1367
02:05:06,886 --> 02:05:11,160
I think you should aim the core of kung fu
and simplify them.

1368
02:05:13,918 --> 02:05:15,828
I get it. But, Professor...

1369
02:05:15,937 --> 02:05:19,308
It's important for you to always simplify
everything you do, Bruce.

1370
02:05:19,418 --> 02:05:23,098
Simplify? So what should I do
to simplify the theories?

1371
02:05:23,213 --> 02:05:25,231
Now, what I'd like to know is,
what is the simplest issue

1372
02:05:25,336 --> 02:05:26,997
of the kung fu theories?

1373
02:05:27,112 --> 02:05:28,322
Please tell me.

1374
02:05:28,435 --> 02:05:30,417
It should be offense and defense.

1375
02:05:32,125 --> 02:05:33,441
How very smart.

1376
02:05:33,552 --> 02:05:35,629
Please take a look
at this dialectic picture.

1377
02:05:35,745 --> 02:05:37,763
It consists of persuasive colors.

1378
02:05:37,868 --> 02:05:40,407
This is a simple way
to make it easy and clear.

1379
02:05:41,593 --> 02:05:45,236
Professor Klein, so keep it simple then?

1380
02:05:45,353 --> 02:05:47,335
Right. You've got to study

1381
02:05:47,441 --> 02:05:50,777
to keep it simple,
and then you have more freedom.

1382
02:05:50,887 --> 02:05:55,053
I must free myself and be relaxed,
simplifying everything,

1383
02:05:55,169 --> 02:05:56,629
eliminating the unnecessary,

1384
02:05:56,736 --> 02:05:58,789
freeing myself from the shackles
of complication.

1385
02:05:58,895 --> 02:06:01,434
Right you are. You said that perfect.

1386
02:06:01,540 --> 02:06:04,174
But when you relax yourself,
you free yourself

1387
02:06:04,290 --> 02:06:06,164
and control your own life.

1388
02:06:06,274 --> 02:06:09,122
Whoever can control the initiative
of the transformation...

1389
02:06:09,234 --> 02:06:11,180
he will find himself definitely.

1390
02:06:11,287 --> 02:06:13,055
Thank you, Professor.

1391
02:06:13,167 --> 02:06:15,280
Kung fu is a special skill,

1392
02:06:15,395 --> 02:06:17,163
an exquisite form of art,

1393
02:06:17,275 --> 02:06:19,708
but not a simple physical exercise.

1394
02:06:19,816 --> 02:06:24,302
It is a kind of art that must combine
wisdom and techniques together.

1395
02:06:24,411 --> 02:06:26,357
The principle of kung fu

1396
02:06:26,465 --> 02:06:29,693
is to utilize your body and mind effectively.

1397
02:06:29,807 --> 02:06:34,531
Yin Yang Tai Chi stands as
the highest of achieved states,

1398
02:06:34,646 --> 02:06:37,316
which indicates the essence
of everything in the universe.

1399
02:06:37,431 --> 02:06:39,971
As for kung fu theory,

1400
02:06:40,076 --> 02:06:41,500
Yin Yang Tai Chi simplifies

1401
02:06:41,609 --> 02:06:44,801
the complicated kung fu
theory into two words:

1402
02:06:44,915 --> 02:06:47,277
"Defense" and "offense."

1403
02:06:47,386 --> 02:06:50,484
In order to reach
the highest state of kung fu,

1404
02:06:50,589 --> 02:06:53,616
you must eliminate
all the extraneous elements

1405
02:06:53,722 --> 02:06:58,138
to reach and maintain the essence
of fighting within the shortest time.

1406
02:06:58,248 --> 02:07:02,034
In fact, it's a kind of
one-two punch, if you will,

1407
02:07:02,147 --> 02:07:04,781
that is very practical in combat

1408
02:07:04,897 --> 02:07:07,295
rather than those elaborate slick moves.

1409
02:07:07,403 --> 02:07:11,783
Meaning, it turns the intangible
into something tangible.

1410
02:07:11,895 --> 02:07:14,363
Jeet Kune Do doesn't have
any fixed set form

1411
02:07:14,470 --> 02:07:17,045
which, in turn, is the best form.

1412
02:07:17,151 --> 02:07:19,061
It doesn't belong to any schools,

1413
02:07:19,169 --> 02:07:23,205
so it's free to use anything from them
without any limitation and forms.

1414
02:07:23,312 --> 02:07:27,277
It's good at using all skills and techniques
which serve their own purpose.

1415
02:07:27,385 --> 02:07:30,970
Instinctive defense
with well-established offense

1416
02:07:31,076 --> 02:07:34,968
is the most straightforward definition
of Jeet Kune Do.

1417
02:07:47,575 --> 02:07:49,629
How many students do you have now?

1418
02:07:49,734 --> 02:07:51,716
No more than 200,

1419
02:07:51,823 --> 02:07:54,422
with four different training sessions.

1420
02:07:54,538 --> 02:07:57,351
This is the evening class.
They're doing their drills right now.

1421
02:07:57,462 --> 02:08:01,010
Bruce, let's talk about
the American fighting competition.

1422
02:08:01,117 --> 02:08:03,337
I think you should take
some time to recover better.

1423
02:08:03,450 --> 02:08:06,892
Don't rush.
- No. I feel fine now.

1424
02:08:07,001 --> 02:08:10,644
Professor, come on.

1425
02:08:10,761 --> 02:08:14,202
Help me analyze. How can I win
the U.S. Championship?

1426
02:08:14,311 --> 02:08:16,186
Bruce, okay.

1427
02:08:16,295 --> 02:08:18,693
I'll give you my opinion then.

1428
02:08:20,298 --> 02:08:21,888
Actually, this time,

1429
02:08:22,004 --> 02:08:24,057
only three of the fighters
will be competitive:

1430
02:08:25,764 --> 02:08:28,755
Rolex, you, and Piao Zhengyi.

1431
02:08:28,862 --> 02:08:32,233
And Rolex looks the best here.

1432
02:08:32,343 --> 02:08:34,598
And, Master Lee, you can only win

1433
02:08:34,711 --> 02:08:36,788
if you have an exchange,
you see, with Master Piao.

1434
02:08:38,922 --> 02:08:41,106
All right. I may go
see him right away then.

1435
02:08:45,676 --> 02:08:47,966
Hey, what's up?

1436
02:08:48,078 --> 02:08:50,511
I want to see your master,
Piao Zhengyi.

1437
02:08:50,619 --> 02:08:52,601
My master can't see anyone.

1438
02:08:54,100 --> 02:08:58,136
Whether he likes it or not,
I must see him now.

1439
02:09:00,401 --> 02:09:02,940
Master.

1440
02:09:03,047 --> 02:09:06,275
Master Piao, sorry to interrupt you.

1441
02:09:06,388 --> 02:09:10,839
I heard that you have competed
in the U.S. Karate competition,

1442
02:09:10,950 --> 02:09:15,187
and you're honored as a genius
of Tae Kwon Do.

1443
02:09:15,300 --> 02:09:18,849
But as far as I know,
you're still not able to rival Rolex.

1444
02:09:18,956 --> 02:09:21,983
If you want to defeat Rolex at all,

1445
02:09:22,089 --> 02:09:24,522
I think you and I should try
to have an exchange.

1446
02:09:24,630 --> 02:09:27,265
Who are you?

1447
02:09:28,324 --> 02:09:29,474
Bruce Lee.

1448
02:09:29,574 --> 02:09:30,819
Bruce Lee.

1449
02:09:30,931 --> 02:09:33,850
Correct. You heard right. Bruce Lee.

1450
02:09:33,960 --> 02:09:36,535
What qualifications do you have
to walk into my dojo?

1451
02:09:36,640 --> 02:09:40,984
Now, you're looking down upon me,
which I understand.

1452
02:09:41,096 --> 02:09:44,253
You are the famous genius
of Tae Kwon Do.

1453
02:09:44,369 --> 02:09:47,811
But I, Bruce Lee... I'm nobody here.

1454
02:09:47,919 --> 02:09:50,138
Let me tell you, if you compete with me,

1455
02:09:50,251 --> 02:09:54,381
I will take you down on the ground
within three rounds.

1456
02:09:54,498 --> 02:09:55,744
I promise you that.

1457
02:11:53,310 --> 02:11:54,971
Stop.

1458
02:12:42,637 --> 02:12:44,406
Stop.

1459
02:12:44,517 --> 02:12:47,366
Ready? Continue.

1460
02:13:10,660 --> 02:13:11,811
Stop.

1461
02:13:22,601 --> 02:13:24,096
Bruce Lee wins.

1462
02:13:49,511 --> 02:13:54,662
Now, in the final round
of the Karate Competition begins.

1463
02:13:54,767 --> 02:13:57,960
Let's welcome Mr. Bruce Lee
from Oakland

1464
02:13:58,074 --> 02:14:00,649
with a big round of applause.

1465
02:14:07,159 --> 02:14:08,654
Now, presenting the champion

1466
02:14:08,761 --> 02:14:11,680
of the last National Karate Competition,

1467
02:14:11,789 --> 02:14:13,700
Mr. Rolex.

1468
02:14:13,809 --> 02:14:16,907
Please give him a round of applause.

1469
02:15:19,498 --> 02:15:20,648
Begin.

1470
02:18:18,012 --> 02:18:19,886
Yes!

1471
02:19:05,564 --> 02:19:08,235
One, two, three.

1472
02:19:08,349 --> 02:19:10,782
Game's over.

1473
02:19:36,894 --> 02:19:40,122
I am Chinese!

1474
02:19:48,730 --> 02:19:53,251
I am Chinese!

1475
02:20:15,987 --> 02:20:19,358
Mr. Rolex, will you please tell us
about your feelings about this match?

1476
02:20:19,468 --> 02:20:20,537
Please tell us.

1477
02:20:20,651 --> 02:20:22,835
It's really hurt my whole career.

1478
02:20:22,950 --> 02:20:26,665
I don't understand
how Bruce Lee could strike me.

1479
02:20:26,779 --> 02:20:28,927
What's more, when I hit on his fist,

1480
02:20:29,042 --> 02:20:31,119
my fist turn powerless all of a sudden.

1481
02:20:31,235 --> 02:20:34,190
But I believe he hasn't

1482
02:20:34,298 --> 02:20:37,146
tried hard on his three kicks.
- That was amazing.

1483
02:20:37,257 --> 02:20:39,476
He has amazing power.
- Thank you very much.

1484
02:20:39,589 --> 02:20:41,607
He should be the winner.

1485
02:20:41,713 --> 02:20:43,208
Thank you.

1486
02:20:43,314 --> 02:20:47,385
An amazing scene just took place here
at the National Karate Competition.

1487
02:20:47,491 --> 02:20:49,081
We have never seen anything like it.

1488
02:20:49,197 --> 02:20:55,215
A young man from China
has completely rewritten the way we fight.

1489
02:20:55,324 --> 02:20:57,437
Journalists cannot figure out...

1490
02:20:57,552 --> 02:20:59,629
Okay, that's all for today.

1491
02:20:59,745 --> 02:21:02,284
You may leave now, everyone.

1492
02:21:14,819 --> 02:21:18,748
It's good. It's absolutely amazing.

1493
02:21:18,857 --> 02:21:21,599
It looks like you have some regrets.

1494
02:21:21,712 --> 02:21:24,524
What are you thinking?

1495
02:21:25,819 --> 02:21:28,632
What a pity. I...

1496
02:21:30,379 --> 02:21:32,812
I should've gone to watch him
fight in the stadium.

1497
02:21:32,921 --> 02:21:35,734
We should go visit this
Chinese guy Bruce Lee maybe.

1498
02:21:35,844 --> 02:21:37,719
He's a Chinese hero, in fact.

1499
02:21:40,127 --> 02:21:41,860
We should go visit him.

1500
02:21:41,971 --> 02:21:43,632
Well, Mr. Harrison, I've got an idea.

1501
02:21:43,747 --> 02:21:45,270
Hollywood needs this kind of action hero.

1502
02:21:45,370 --> 02:21:46,903
George,

1503
02:21:47,019 --> 02:21:50,046
I have to say you are
a brilliant businessman.

1504
02:21:50,152 --> 02:21:51,505
Yeah? I hope so.

1505
02:22:22,248 --> 02:22:24,158
Bruce Lee. Well, well, well.

1506
02:22:24,267 --> 02:22:26,451
Hey, hello, Mr. Lee.
- Hi. Hello.

1507
02:22:26,565 --> 02:22:28,025
We're here to congratulate you.

1508
02:22:28,131 --> 02:22:29,914
We've been waiting for you for a while.
- What...

1509
02:22:30,014 --> 02:22:31,674
Come on. You've never heard of him before?

1510
02:22:31,787 --> 02:22:32,937
You're kidding me, right?

1511
02:22:33,040 --> 02:22:34,737
He's with Robert.

1512
02:22:34,850 --> 02:22:37,592
Big Hollywood producer of stars.

1513
02:22:37,705 --> 02:22:40,862
Very important man.
Let's go and talk to him.

1514
02:22:42,021 --> 02:22:43,374
James?

1515
02:22:44,562 --> 02:22:47,233
Sure you should go. Go see him.

1516
02:22:47,348 --> 02:22:50,267
Okay. I'll go.

1517
02:22:53,509 --> 02:22:56,179
It can't be bad that someone
from Hollywood asked to meet Bruce.

1518
02:22:56,294 --> 02:22:58,965
Let's go wait for the good news.

1519
02:22:59,079 --> 02:23:02,176
Let me introduce you.
This is George from Hollywood.

1520
02:23:02,282 --> 02:23:05,308
Hello, Mr. Lee.
I've been watching you for a long time.

1521
02:23:05,415 --> 02:23:07,112
What can I do for you
this afternoon?

1522
02:23:07,225 --> 02:23:08,958
Well, but, of course,

1523
02:23:09,069 --> 02:23:10,909
with your specific permission,

1524
02:23:11,019 --> 02:23:13,096
I'd like to make a movie
of your great performance.

1525
02:23:16,241 --> 02:23:17,558
Why?

1526
02:23:17,668 --> 02:23:20,932
I saw you win the championship on TV.

1527
02:23:21,045 --> 02:23:23,099
I admire your
kung fu skills very much.

1528
02:23:23,203 --> 02:23:25,185
Your movements were so fast
in the game,

1529
02:23:25,292 --> 02:23:26,822
I'd like to record it for other players.

1530
02:23:26,928 --> 02:23:30,643
But my real purpose,
to be honest with you,

1531
02:23:30,757 --> 02:23:34,757
is to work together
in some other field someday.

1532
02:23:34,865 --> 02:23:37,464
You mean, shooting movies?

1533
02:23:37,581 --> 02:23:40,085
Yes. Kung fu movies.

1534
02:23:40,191 --> 02:23:43,491
You have a chance
to showcase your work in Hollywood.

1535
02:23:43,603 --> 02:23:46,486
What better way to showcase
your kung fu performance?

1536
02:23:47,606 --> 02:23:49,445
Well, this is not a bad idea.

1537
02:23:49,556 --> 02:23:50,837
You persuaded me.

1538
02:23:50,947 --> 02:23:52,716
Ah, that's great, Mr. Lee.

1539
02:23:52,827 --> 02:23:55,367
Wouldn't you say we have a deal
between us, don't you think?

1540
02:23:55,473 --> 02:23:57,063
All right. I'll listen to you.

1541
02:23:57,179 --> 02:23:58,805
That's great.

1542
02:23:58,919 --> 02:24:00,902
We should have a drink
to celebrate, don't you think?

1543
02:24:01,008 --> 02:24:02,397
Sounds good.
- Let's go.

1544
02:24:38,570 --> 02:24:40,303
That's great.

1545
02:24:40,415 --> 02:24:44,131
Mr. Kato's appearance
definitely gives us a fresh impression.

1546
02:24:44,244 --> 02:24:48,838
Mr. Kato, you're a great warrior
nobody can match.

1547
02:24:48,943 --> 02:24:50,569
Don't you understand?

1548
02:24:50,685 --> 02:24:53,568
Wearing the mask will only
boost your charm as a warrior

1549
02:24:53,678 --> 02:24:56,040
and show a kind of mysterious style.

1550
02:24:56,150 --> 02:24:57,882
You may choose whatever you like

1551
02:24:57,995 --> 02:25:01,817
from all these masks
we prepared for you here.

